review:
wow, great stuff Mobius! I like how much you did to the song, nicely done. A lot of people try to add in new elements of their own, and their remix comes off like a watered down version of the original. By the way, I was reading someone\'s review on here, and I think they are a complete idiot. Try reading what the Letter means by the remixes, before you post.

for those that don\'t know what the letter S means, next to his remix, it means:

\'S - Remix does not contain any additional material other than the source files provided by the official NIN website, and is therefore considered safe for inclusion on an official release or \"Halo\".\'

Wow! This really works for me all around -- as if Resnor said, \&quot;Hey Ewun, mix this song for me, will ya? Thanks!\&quot;
Lots of passion for the music is what I hear in this remix. And mystery. What\'s that voice at the end saying? Unconventionally glitchy, GREAT!
Sombody throw some money at this kid so he makes more music. :)

This was a DAMN good mix. I instantly thought of blending Vessel and Closer together when I first heard the first verse of Vessel, but you beat me to it. Granted, I don\'t have the mixing prowess to develop an even remotely good mix, but I have ideas.

This mix did a lot of what I personally had in mind though, and in most cases in the song did better than I had imagined. The only thing I want someone to do is blend the first verses of both Closer and Vessel together, since they go together nicely.

\&quot;I let you put in it my mouth\&quot;
\&quot;You let me violate you\&quot;
\&quot;I let it get under my skin\&quot;
\&quot;You let me desecrate you\&quot;
\&quot;I let you pump it in my veins\&quot;
[Right here though, when Trent half-hisses the word \'veins\' it\'s not probable to put in the other  line from Closer, so I guess it would just carry over or something]

Anyway, you see what I mean. XD That really has nothing to do with your mix, just a thought I had that I wanted to get out there. But overall I highly enjoyed your mix and can\'t say anything bad about it.

Also to add onto the &quot;differences&quot; section, the intro to the mix was re-added.

(In v1.0, it was cut out.)

The Nyx Avatar quotes used are (in order):

&quot;Alongside time, exists fate. The bearer of cruelty.&quot;

&quot;Celebrate life's grandour. It's brilliance, it's magnificence.&quot;

&quot;To find the one true path, one must seek guidance amidst uncertainty.&quot;

&quot;It requires great courage to look at one's self honestly, and forge one's own path.&quot;

&quot;One of life's greatest blessings, is the ability to persue one's goal.&quot;

&quot;Only with strength can one endure suffering and torment.&quot;

&quot;The silent voice within one's heart whispers the most profound wisdom.&quot;

&quot;The moment man devoured the fruit of knowledge, he sealed his fate.&quot;

&quot;Man clings to a dim hope.&quot;

&quot;Beyond the beaten path lies the abosolute end. It matters not who you are...Death awaits you.&quot;

I do believe that covers it all!
